Calcareous ring long, radial and interradial main plates weakly fragmented (
Fig. 3C
). Radial elements elongated with an anterior projection and anterior notch, and with paired posterior, weakly fragmented prolongations. Interradial elements also long, without posterior prolongations, with anterior projection, shortest in ventro-lateral elements. One Polian vesicle in medioventral, single stone canal in mediodorsal position. Well-matured gonad situated in posterior mid-body, in single clump on dorsal mesentery, tubules not branched. Gonad lacking ossicles.
